com.intel.fightclub.ui.screens.program.fragment.configure

Class DistancePickerDialogFragment

  • java.lang.Object
    • android.support.v4.app.Fragment
      • android.support.v4.app.DialogFragment
        • com.intel.fightclub.ui.screens.program.fragment.configure.DistancePickerDialogFragment
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    android.content.ComponentCallbacks, android.content.DialogInterface.OnCancelListener, android.content.DialogInterface.OnDismissListener, android.view.View.OnCreateContextMenuListener

    public class DistancePickerDialogFragment
extends android.support.v4.app.DialogFragment
    Distance picker dialog.

    Fragment allows to select distance between max and min values. Distance is provided in exact form, by using two integer variables for integer and fractional part. Unit system (imperial or metric) is not used in business logic and used only for visual indication in which units the selection is made. Max and min values are compared only against integer part of actual distance. Fractional picker automatically resets to 0, if max integer value is select.

    Selected value is propagated through DistancePickerDialogFragment.DistanceConfirmedListener only when dialog is confirmed. This way if dialog is cancelled, old values are kept.

    Min and max distance is provided just with integer part, fractional is set as zero.

    Values from integer picker are used directly, for fractional picker translation from index to value mFractionOptions is used.
